  nickname: eph
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 69cda689d36a6b64ca4a020e1d829e9f, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Paul\u2019s Introduction"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Introduction"
      number: 1
      content: 'Dear friends,My name is Paul, and I was chosen by God to be an apostle
        of Jesus, the Messiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: "2: Our Sonship and the Father\u2019s Plan"
      title: "Our Sonship and the Father\u2019s Plan"
      number: 2
      content: "I\u2019m writing this letter to all the devoted believers [[COMMENT(0)]]
        who have been made holy  by being one with Jesus, the Anointed One.May God
        himself, the heavenly Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, release grace over
        you and impart total well-being  into your lives."
      comments:
      - number: 1:2
        content: "  Recent manuscripts add the words \u201Cthose who are in Ephesus.\u201D
          The oldest manuscripts have \u201Cto the Ephesians\u201D written in the
          margin. This would reinforce the theory that it is meant to be read and
          distributed to all the churches. Although the book bears the name \u201CEphesians,\u201D
          some scholars believe that this letter could be the missing letter to the
          Laodiceans mentioned in  . Regardless, Ephesians contains crucial truths
          for believers worldwide.      Or \u201Cto the saints [holy ones] and the
          faithful in Christ Jesus.\u201D Notice that God is the one who makes us
          holy, but our response is to be \u201Cfaithful\u201D (or \u201Cdevoted\u201D).     
          Or \u201Cpeace.\u201D The Hebrew concept of peace means much more than
          tranquility.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Every spiritual blessing in the heavenly realm has already been lavished
        upon us as a love gift from our wonderful heavenly Father, the Father of
        our Lord Jesus\u2014all because he sees us wrapped into Christ. This is why
        we celebrate him [[COMMENT(0)]] with all our hearts!"
      comments:
      - number: 1:3
        content: "  Or \u201Cbless\u201D (or \u201Cblessed be God\u201D).    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And in love he chose us before he laid the foundation of the universe!
        [[COMMENT(0)]] Because of his great love, he ordained us, so that we would
        be seen as holy in his eyes with an unstained innocence.
      comments:
      - number: 1:4
        content: "  There is an alternate Greek translation of the unique wording
          of this verse that could be translated \u201CHe chose us to be a \u2018word\u2019
          before the fall of the world.\u201D The Greek word for \u201Cchose\u201D
          is  , which is a form of    (speak). The word for \u201Cfall\u201D (Adam\u2019s
          fall) is  , which can mean \u201Cfalling down,\u201D but is usually translated
          as \u201Cfoundation\u201D (of the world).    "
    - name: '5-6: '
      title: 
      number: 5-6
      content: "For it was always in his perfect plan [[COMMENT(0)]] to adopt  us
        as his delightful children, through our union with Jesus, the Anointed One,
        so that his tremendous love that cascades over us would glorify his grace
        \u2014for the same love he has for the Beloved, Jesus, he has for us. And
        this unfolding plan brings him great pleasure!"
      comments:
      - number: "1:5\u20136"
        content: "  Or \u201CHe marked out our horizon [destiny] beforehand.\u201D     
          The Aramaic reads \u201Cto establish us.\u201D      Or \u201Cto praise
          upon praise of the glory of his grace.\u201D    "
    - name: '5-6: '
      title: 
      number: 5-6
      content: "For it was always in his perfect plan [[COMMENT(0)]] to adopt  us
        as his delightful children, through our union with Jesus, the Anointed One,
        so that his tremendous love that cascades over us would glorify his grace
        \u2014for the same love he has for the Beloved, Jesus, he has for us. And
        this unfolding plan brings him great pleasure!"
      comments:
      - number: "1:5\u20136"
        content: "  Or \u201CHe marked out our horizon [destiny] beforehand.\u201D     
          The Aramaic reads \u201Cto establish us.\u201D      Or \u201Cto praise
          upon praise of the glory of his grace.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Since we are now joined to Christ, we have been given the treasures
        of redemption by his blood\u2014the total cancellation [[COMMENT(0)]] of
        our sins\u2014all because of the cascading riches  of his grace. "
      comments:
      - number: 1:7
        content: "  Or \u201Cforgiveness.\u201D The Greek word    means \u201Cto
          send away\u201D or \u201Cto set free\u201D (from bondage).      The Greek
          word for \u201Criches\u201D () is also used to describe God\u2019s wisdom
          and knowledge in  . Just as God is all-knowing and has all-wisdom, so he
          has untold riches of grace available for his children.    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'This superabundant grace is already powerfully working in us, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        releasing all forms of wisdom and practical understanding. '
      comments:
      - number: 1:8
        content: "  Or \u201Clavished on us.\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And through the revelation of the Anointed One, he unveiled his secret
        desires to us\u2014the hidden mystery of his long-range plan, which he was
        delighted to implement from the very beginning of time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And because of God\u2019s unfailing purpose, this detailed plan will
        reign supreme through every period of time until the fulfillment of all the
        ages finally reaches its climax\u2014when God makes all things new [[COMMENT(0)]]
        in all of heaven and earth through Jesus Christ."
      comments:
      - number: 1:10
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. The Greek text states \u201CGod
          will gather together all things in fulfillment in Christ.\u201D That is,
          God will unite all things under the headship of Christ.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Through our union with Christ we too have been claimed by God as
        his own inheritance. [[COMMENT(0)]] Before we were even born, he gave us
        our destiny;  that we would fulfill the plan of God who always accomplishes
        every purpose and plan in his heart. '
      comments:
      - number: 1:11
        content: "  The Greek construction of this phrase can mean either that God
          appointed us (Gr.  , chosen by casting lots) to be his inheritance, or
          that we have been appointed an inheritance.      Or \u201Cestate.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "God\u2019s purpose was that we Jews, who were the first to long for
        the messianic hope, would be the first to believe in the Anointed One and
        bring great praise and glory to God!"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And because of him, when you who are not Jews heard the revelation
        [[COMMENT(0)]] of truth, you believed in the wonderful news of salvation.
        Now we have been stamped with the seal of the promised Holy Spirit. '
      comments:
      - number: 1:13
        content: "  The Greek text is    or \u201Cword of God.\u201D      Some Aramaic
          manuscripts add here \u201Cwho was announced by the angels.\u201D    "
    - name: '14: Paul Prays for the Spirit of Wisdom and Revelation'
      title: Paul Prays for the Spirit of Wisdom and Revelation
      number: 14
      content: "He is given to us like an engagement ring, [[COMMENT(0)]] as the
        first installment of what\u2019s coming! He is our hope-promise of a future
        inheritance  which seals us until we have all of redemption\u2019s promises
        and experience complete freedom\u2014all for the supreme glory and honor
        of God!"
      comments:
      - number: 1:14
        content: "  The Greek word used here can be translated \u201Cpledge,\u201D
          \u201Cdown payment\u201D or \u201Cengagement ring.\u201D      The Aramaic
          word used for \u201Cinheritance\u201D can also be translated \u201Cdividend.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Because of this, since I first heard about your strong faith in the
        Lord Jesus Christ and your tender love toward all his devoted ones, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'my heart is always full and overflowing with thanks to God for you
        as I constantly remember you in my prayers. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 1:16
        content: "  The literal Aramaic text can be translated \u201CI began confessing
          on your behalf and praying.\u201D    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: I pray that the Father of glory, the God of our Lord Jesus Christ,
        would impart to you the riches of the Spirit of wisdom and the Spirit of
        revelation [[COMMENT(0)]] to know him through your deepening intimacy with
        him.
      comments:
      - number: 1:17
        content: "  Or \u201Cdiscovery.\u201D    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "I pray that the light of God will illuminate the eyes of your imagination,
        [[COMMENT(0)]] flooding you with light, until you experience the full revelation
        of the hope of his calling \u2014that is, the wealth of God\u2019s glorious
        inheritances that he finds in us, his holy ones!"
      comments:
      - number: 1:18
        content: "  Or \u201Cinnermost\u201D (heart).      Or \u201Cto which he is
          calling you.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "I pray that you will continually experience the immeasurable greatness
        of God\u2019s power made available to you through faith. Then your lives
        will be an advertisement of this immense power as it works through you! This
        is the mighty power "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'that was released when God raised Christ from the dead and exalted
        him [[COMMENT(0)]] to the place of highest honor and supreme authority  in
        the heavenly realm! '
      comments:
      - number: 1:20
        content: "  Or \u201Che seated him\u201D (enthroned).      Or \u201Cat his
          right hand,\u201D a metaphor for the place of honor and authority.    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And now he is exalted as first above every ruler, authority, government,
        and realm of power in existence! He is gloriously enthroned over every name
        that is ever praised, [[COMMENT(0)]] not only in this age,  but in the age
        that is coming! '
      comments:
      - number: 1:21
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic.      The Aramaic word can be
          translated \u201Cuniverse.\u201D      As translated from the Aramaic.    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And he alone is the leader and source of everything needed in the
        church. God has put everything beneath the authority of Jesus Christ [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        and has given him the highest rank above all others. '
      comments:
      - number: 1:22
        content: "  Both Greek and Aramaic texts use the figure of speech \u201Cunder
          his feet,\u201D which means he has conquered, subdued, and now rules over
          them.    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And now we, his church, are his body on the earth and that which fills
        him who is being filled by it! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 1:23
        content: '  That is, as we are those who are filled (completed) by Christ,
          we also complete (fill) him. What a wonderful and humbling mystery is revealed
          by this verse.  '
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Power Raised Us from the Dead"
      title: "God\u2019s Power Raised Us from the Dead"
      number: 1
      content: 'And his fullness fills you, even though you were once like corpses,
        [[COMMENT(0)]] dead in your sins and offenses. '
      comments:
      - number: 2:1
        content: '  As translated literally from the Greek.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "It wasn\u2019t that long ago that you lived in the religion, customs,
        and values [[COMMENT(0)]] of this world,  obeying the dark ruler of the earthly
        realm who fills the atmosphere with his authority, and works diligently in
        the hearts of those who are disobedient to the truth of God. "
      comments:
      - number: 2:2
        content: "  The Aramaic can be translated \u201Cthe worldliness of this world.\u201D     
          The Aramaic phrase can also refer to the authority of secular governments.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The corruption that was in us from birth was expressed through the
        deeds and desires of our self-life. We lived by whatever natural cravings
        and thoughts our minds dictated, living as rebellious children subject to
        God\u2019s wrath like everyone else."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But God still loved us with such great love. He is so rich in compassion
        and mercy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Even when we were dead and doomed in our many sins, he united us
        into the very life of Christ and saved us by his wonderful grace! '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: He raised us up with Christ the exalted One, and we ascended with
        him into the glorious perfection and authority of the heavenly realm, for
        we are now co-seated [[COMMENT(0)]] as one with Christ!
      comments:
      - number: 2:6
        content: "  To be \u201Cplaced\u201D or \u201Cseated\u201D in heaven means
          we have been given the perfection and authority to be there.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Throughout the coming ages [[COMMENT(0)]] we will be the visible
        display of the infinite riches of his grace and kindness, which was showered
        upon us in Jesus Christ. '
      comments:
      - number: 2:7
        content: "  The Aramaic can be translated \u201Cuniverses.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For by grace you have been saved by faith. Nothing you did could
        ever earn this salvation, for it was the love gift [[COMMENT(0)]] from God
        that brought us to Christ! '
      comments:
      - number: 2:8
        content: "  The Aramaic word for \u201Cgift\u201D is    and comes from the
          Aramaic word  , which means \u201Clove.\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: So no one will ever be able to boast, for salvation is never a reward
        for good works or human striving.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: A New Humanity'
      title: A New Humanity
      number: 10
      content: We have become his poetry, [[COMMENT(0)]] a re-created people that
        will fulfill the destiny he has given each of us, for we are joined to Jesus,
        the Anointed One. Even before we were born, God planned in advance our destiny
        and the good works  we would do to fulfill it!
      comments:
      - number: 2:10
        content: "  The beautiful Greek word used here is translated \u201Cpoem\u201D
          or \u201Cpoetry.\u201D Our lives are the beautiful poetry written by God
          that will speak forth all that he desires in life.      Although implied,
          these good works make up our destiny. As we yield to God, our prearranged
          destiny comes to pass and we are rewarded for simply doing what he wanted
          us to accomplish.    "
    - name: '11-12: '
      title: 
      number: 11-12
      content: "So don\u2019t forget that you were not born as Jews and were uncircumcised
        (circumcision itself is just a work of man\u2019s hands); you had none of
        the Jewish covenants and laws; you were foreigners to Israel\u2019s incredible
        heritage; [[COMMENT(0)]] you were without the covenants and prophetic promises
        of the Messiah, the promised hope, and without God."
      comments:
      - number: "2:11\u201312"
        content: "  Or \u201Cfreedom,\u201D or \u201Ccommonwealth.\u201D    "
    - name: '11-12: '
      title: 
      number: 11-12
      content: "So don\u2019t forget that you were not born as Jews and were uncircumcised
        (circumcision itself is just a work of man\u2019s hands); you had none of
        the Jewish covenants and laws; you were foreigners to Israel\u2019s incredible
        heritage; [[COMMENT(0)]] you were without the covenants and prophetic promises
        of the Messiah, the promised hope, and without God."
      comments:
      - number: "2:11\u201312"
        content: "  Or \u201Cfreedom,\u201D or \u201Ccommonwealth.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Yet look at you now! Everything is new! Although you were once distant
        and far away from God, now you have been brought delightfully close to him
        through the sacred blood of Jesus\u2014you have actually been united to Christ!"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Our reconciling \u201CPeace\u201D is Jesus! He has made Jew and non-Jew
        one in Christ. By dying as our sacrifice, he has broken down every wall of
        prejudice that separated us and has now made us equal through our union with
        Christ. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Ethnic hatred has been dissolved by the crucifixion of his precious
        body on the cross. The legal code that stood condemning every one of us has
        now been repealed by his command. His triune essence has made peace between
        us by starting over\u2014forming [[COMMENT(0)]] one new race of humanity, 
        Jews and non-Jews fused together in himself!"
      comments:
      - number: 2:15
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. The Greek is \u201Cto create
          in himself one new man.\u201D      Or \u201Cone new man.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Two have now become one, and we live restored to God and reconciled
        in the body of Christ. Through his crucifixion, hatred died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For the Messiah has come to preach this sweet message of peace to
        you, [[COMMENT(0)]] the ones who were distant, and to those who are near. '
      comments:
      - number: 2:17
        content: "  This is Paul\u2019s paraphrase of  .    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And now, because we are united to Christ, we both have equal and direct
        access in the realm of the Holy Spirit to come before the Father!
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So, you are not foreigners or guests, but rather you are the children
        of the city of the holy ones, [[COMMENT(0)]] with all the rights as family
        members of the household of God. '
      comments:
      - number: 2:19
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: You are rising like the perfectly fitted stones of the temple; [[COMMENT(0)]]
        and your lives have been built up together upon the foundation laid by the
        apostles and prophets, and best of all, you are connected to the Head Cornerstone
        of the building, the Anointed One, Jesus Christ himself!
      comments:
      - number: 2:20
        content: "  The \u201Ctemple\u201D is not found in the text here, but is
          explicitly mentioned in v.  .  "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'This entire building is under construction and is continually growing
        under his supervision until it rises up completed as the holy temple of the
        Lord himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: This means that God is transforming each one of you into the Holy
        of Holies, his dwelling place, through the power of the Holy Spirit living
        in you!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Divine Mystery'
      title: The Divine Mystery
      number: 1
      content: 'Beloved friends, because of my love for Jesus Christ, I am now his
        prisoner for the sake of all of you who are not Jews, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'so that you will hear the gospel that God has entrusted to me to
        share with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For this wonderful mystery, which I briefly described, was given
        to me by divine revelation, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: so that whenever you read it you will be able to understand my revelation
        and insight into the secret mystery of the Messiah.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'There has never been a generation that has been given the detailed
        understanding of this glorious and divine mystery until now. He kept it a
        secret until this generation. God is revealing it only now to his sacred
        apostles and prophets by the Holy Spirit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Here\u2019s the secret: The gospel of grace has made you, non-Jewish
        believers, into coheirs of his promise through your union with him. And you
        have now become members of his body\u2014one with the Anointed One!"
      comments: []
    - name: '7-8: '
      title: 
      number: 7-8
      content: I have been made a messenger of this wonderful news by the gift of
        grace that works through me. Even though I am the least significant of all
        his holy believers, this grace-gift was imparted when the manifestation of
        his power came upon me. Grace alone empowers me so that I can boldly preach
        this wonderful message to non-Jewish people, sharing with them the unfading,
        [[COMMENT(0)]] inexhaustible riches of Christ, which are beyond comprehension.
      comments:
      - number: "3:7\u20138"
        content: "  The word    comes from an Aramaic word which can also be translated
          \u201Cunquestionable\u201D or \u201Cwithout fault.\u201D The Greek uses
          the word  .    "
    - name: '7-8: '
      title: 
      number: 7-8
      content: I have been made a messenger of this wonderful news by the gift of
        grace that works through me. Even though I am the least significant of all
        his holy believers, this grace-gift was imparted when the manifestation of
        his power came upon me. Grace alone empowers me so that I can boldly preach
        this wonderful message to non-Jewish people, sharing with them the unfading,
        [[COMMENT(0)]] inexhaustible riches of Christ, which are beyond comprehension.
      comments:
      - number: "3:7\u20138"
        content: "  The word    comes from an Aramaic word which can also be translated
          \u201Cunquestionable\u201D or \u201Cwithout fault.\u201D The Greek uses
          the word  .    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'My passion is to enlighten every person to this divine mystery. It
        was hidden for ages past until now, and kept a secret in the heart of God,
        the Creator of all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The purpose of this was to unveil before every throne and rank of
        angelic orders in the heavenly realm God\u2019s full and diverse wisdom revealed
        through the church. [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 3:10
        content: "  The church is the \u201Cuniversity of the angels\u201D and every
          believer is a \u201Cprofessor\u201D teaching the heavenly realm the mysteries
          and wonders of the grace of God. The angels investigate through our lives
          the treasures of grace, like the cherubim who gaze upon the mercy seat.
          See  .    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'This perfectly wise plan was destined from eternal ages and fulfilled
        completely in our Lord Jesus Christ, so that now '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "we have boldness through him, [[COMMENT(0)]] and free access as kings 
        before the Father because of our complete confidence in Christ\u2019s faithfulness."
      comments:
      - number: 3:12
        content: "  The Greek words used here can be translated, \u201Cfreedom of
          speech to say whatever you want with boldness.\u201D      The Aramaic text
          can be translated \u201Cwe have kingship.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: Paul Prays for Love to Overflow'
      title: Paul Prays for Love to Overflow
      number: 13
      content: My dear friends, I pray that you will remain strong and not be discouraged
        or ashamed by all that I suffer on your behalf, for it is for your glory.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So I kneel humbly in awe before the Father of our Lord Jesus, the
        Messiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the perfect Father of every father and child [[COMMENT(0)]] in heaven
        and on the earth. '
      comments:
      - number: 3:15
        content: "  Translated from the Aramaic. It could also be translated \u201Cthe
          perfect Father of every people group.\u201D The Greek word for \u201Cfather\u201D
          and the word for \u201Cfamily\u201D are quite similar, which indicates
          that every family finds its source in the Father.    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And I pray that he would unveil within you the unlimited riches of
        his glory and favor until supernatural strength floods your innermost being
        with his divine might and explosive power.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Then, by constantly using your faith, the life of Christ will be released
        deep inside you, and the resting place of his love will become the very source
        and root of your life.
      comments: []
    - name: '18-19: '
      title: 
      number: 18-19
      content: "Then you will be empowered to discover what every holy one experiences\u2014the
        great magnitude [[COMMENT(0)]] of the astonishing love of Christ in all its
        dimensions. How deeply intimate and far-reaching is his love! How enduring
        and inclusive it is! Endless love beyond measurement that transcends our
        understanding\u2014this extravagant love pours into you until you are filled
        to overflowing with the fullness of God!"
      comments:
      - number: "3:18\u201319"
        content: "  Or \u201Cexcellence.\u201D    "
    - name: '18-19: '
      title: 
      number: 18-19
      content: "Then you will be empowered to discover what every holy one experiences\u2014the
        great magnitude [[COMMENT(0)]] of the astonishing love of Christ in all its
        dimensions. How deeply intimate and far-reaching is his love! How enduring
        and inclusive it is! Endless love beyond measurement that transcends our
        understanding\u2014this extravagant love pours into you until you are filled
        to overflowing with the fullness of God!"
      comments:
      - number: "3:18\u201319"
        content: "  Or \u201Cexcellence.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Never doubt God\u2019s mighty power to work in you and accomplish
        all this. He will achieve infinitely more than your greatest request, your
        most unbelievable dream, and exceed your wildest imagination! [[COMMENT(0)]]
        He will outdo them all, for his miraculous power constantly energizes you."
      comments:
      - number: 3:20
        content: '  See  .  '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now we offer up to God all the glorious praise that rises from every
        church in every generation through Jesus Christ\u2014and all that will yet
        be manifest through time and eternity. Amen!"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Our Divine Calling'
      title: Our Divine Calling
      number: 1
      content: 'As a prisoner of the Lord, [[COMMENT(0)]] I plead with you to walk
        holy, in a way that is suitable to your high rank, given to you in your divine
        calling. '
      comments:
      - number: 4:1
        content: '  Paul wrote this letter while a prisoner in Rome because of his
          faith in Christ. See  .    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'With tender humility and quiet patience, always demonstrate gentleness
        and generous [[COMMENT(0)]] love toward one another, especially toward those
        who may try your patience. '
      comments:
      - number: 4:2
        content: "  The Aramaic word literally means \u201Cstretching.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Be faithful to guard the sweet harmony of the Holy Spirit among you
        in the bonds of peace, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: being one body and one spirit, as you were all called into the same
        glorious hope of divine destiny.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For the Lord God is one, and so are we, for we share in one faith,
        one baptism, and one Father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: The Grace-Gifts of Christ'
      title: The Grace-Gifts of Christ
      number: 6
      content: And he is the perfect Father who leads us all, works through us all,
        and lives in us all!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he has generously given each one of us supernatural grace, according
        to the size of the gift of Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "This is why he says:\u201CHe ascends into the heavenly heightstaking
        his many captured ones with him, [[COMMENT(0)]]and gifts were given to men.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 4:8
        content: "  Or \u201Che captured captivity.\u201D      Or \u201Cmen were
          given as gifts.\u201D See  .    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He \u201Cascended\u201D means that he returned to heaven, after he
        had first descended from the heights of heaven, even to the lower regions,
        namely, the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The same one who descended is also the one who ascended above the
        heights of heaven, in order to begin the restoration and fulfillment [[COMMENT(0)]]
        of all things.
      comments:
      - number: 4:10
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. The Greek text says \u201Cthat
          he might fill all things.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he has appointed some with grace to be apostles, and some with
        grace to be prophets, and some with grace to be evangelists, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        and some with grace to be pastors,  and some with grace to be teachers.   '
      comments:
      - number: 4:11
        content: "  The Aramaic can be translated \u201Cpreachers.\u201D      Or
          \u201Cshepherds.\u201D      The Aramaic can be translated \u201Cwise orators.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And their calling is to nurture and prepare all the holy believers
        to do their own works of ministry, and as they do this they will enlarge
        and build up the body of Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: These grace ministries will function until we all attain oneness into
        the faith, until we all experience the fullness of what it means to know
        the Son of God, [[COMMENT(0)]] and finally we become one into a perfect man 
        with the full dimensions of spiritual maturity and fully developed into the
        abundance of Christ.
      comments:
      - number: 4:13
        content: "  The Greek literally means \u201Cuntil we have the full knowledge
          of the Son of God.\u201D      The Hebrew and Aramaic word for \u201Cperfect\u201D
          is  , and the word implies that perfection cannot come to the body of Christ
          without the example and teaching of these five ministries\u2014apostles,
          prophets, evangelists, pastors, and teachers. To ignore these five ministry
          gifts of the ascended Christ for today is to despise the gifts that God
          has given to the church.    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And then our immaturity will end! And we will not be easily shaken
        by trouble, nor led astray by novel teachings or by the false doctrines of
        deceivers [[COMMENT(0)]] who teach clever lies. '
      comments:
      - number: 4:14
        content: "  The Greek literally means \u201Cdice-playing gamblers.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: But instead we will remain strong and always sincere in our love as
        we express the truth. All our direction and ministries will flow from Christ
        and lead us deeper into him, the anointed Head of his body, the church.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Our New Life in Christ'
      title: Our New Life in Christ
      number: 16
      content: "For his \u201Cbody\u201D has been formed in his image and is closely
        joined together and constantly connected as one. And every member has been
        given divine gifts to contribute to the growth of all; and as these gifts
        operate effectively throughout the whole body, we are built up and made perfect
        in love."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So with the wisdom given to me from the Lord I say: You should not
        live like the unbelievers around you who walk in their empty delusions. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 4:17
        content: "  Or \u201Copinions.\u201D    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Their corrupted logic has been clouded because their hearts are so
        far from God\u2014their blinded understanding and deep-seated moral darkness
        keeps them from the true knowledge of God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Because of spiritual apathy, they surrender their lives to lewdness,
        impurity, and sexual obsession.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But this is not the way of life that Christ has unfolded within you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: If you have really experienced the Anointed One, and heard his truth,
        it will be seen in your life; for we know that the ultimate reality [[COMMENT(0)]]
        is embodied in Jesus!
      comments:
      - number: 4:21
        content: "  Or \u201Cultimate learning.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And he has taught you to let go of the lifestyle of the ancient man,
        [[COMMENT(0)]] the old self-life, which was corrupted by sinful and deceitful
        desires that spring from delusions. '
      comments:
      - number: 4:22
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now it\u2019s time to be made new by every revelation that\u2019s
        been given to you. [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 4:23
        content: "  Or \u201Cin the spirit of your revelation.\u201D    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And to be transformed as you embrace the glorious Christ-within as
        your new life and live in union with him! For God has re-created you all
        over again in his perfect righteousness, and you now belong to him in the
        realm of true holiness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: So discard every form of dishonesty and lying so that you will be
        known as one who always speaks the truth, for we all belong to one another.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But don\u2019t let the passion of your emotions [[COMMENT(0)]] lead
        you to sin! Don\u2019t let anger control you or be fuel for revenge, not
        for even a day. "
      comments:
      - number: 4:26
        content: "  The Aramaic word    means \u201Cto shake\u201D or \u201Cto tremble.\u201D
          It is a word used for any strong emotion, but usually refers to anger.    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Don\u2019t give the slanderous accuser, the Devil, an opportunity
        to manipulate you! "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "If any one of you has stolen from someone else, never do it again.
        Instead, be industrious, earning an honest living, and then you\u2019ll have
        enough to bless those in need."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: And never let ugly or hateful words come from your mouth, but instead
        let your words become beautiful gifts [[COMMENT(0)]] that encourage others;
        do this by speaking words of grace to help them.
      comments:
      - number: 4:29
        content: "  Or \u201Cconstructive.\u201D    "
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The Holy Spirit of God has sealed you in Jesus Christ until you experience
        your full salvation. So never grieve the Spirit of God or take for granted
        his holy influence in your life. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 4:30
        content: "  The Greek manuscripts have \u201Cdo not grieve,\u201D while the
          Aramaic text reads \u201Cdo not limit his scope.\u201D This translation
          includes both concepts.    "
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Lay aside bitter words, temper tantrums, revenge, profanity, and
        insults. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "But instead be kind [[COMMENT(0)]] and affectionate toward one another.
        Has God graciously forgiven you? Then graciously forgive one another in the
        depths of Christ\u2019s love."
      comments:
      - number: 4:32
        content: "  The Aramaic word for \u201Ckind\u201D can also be translated
          \u201Csweet.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Living in God\u2019s Love"
      title: "Living in God\u2019s Love"
      number: 1
      content: 'Be imitators of God in everything you do, [[COMMENT(0)]] for then
        you will represent your Father as his beloved sons and daughters. '
      comments:
      - number: 5:1
        content: '  The Greek word    frequently depicts an actor playing a role.
          God wants us to mimic him and be filled with his thoughts, his love, his
          deeds, and his character.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And continue to walk surrendered to the extravagant love of Christ,
        for he surrendered his life as a sacrifice for us. His great love for us
        was pleasing to God, like an aroma of adoration\u2014a sweet healing fragrance.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 5:2
        content: "  The Aramaic word for \u201Cfragrance\u201D can also be translated
          \u201Chealing balm.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And have nothing to do with sexual immorality, lust, or greed\u2014for
        you are his holy ones and let no one be able to accuse you of them in any
        form. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Guard your speech. Forsake obscenities and worthless insults; these
        are nonsensical words that bring disgrace and are unnecessary. Instead, let
        worship fill your heart and spill out in your words.
      comments: []
    - name: "5: Living in God\u2019s Light"
      title: "Living in God\u2019s Light"
      number: 5
      content: "For it has been made clear to you already that the kingdom of God
        cannot be accessed by anyone who is guilty of sexual sin, or who is impure
        or greedy\u2014for greed is the essence of idolatry. How could they expect
        to have an inheritance in Christ\u2019s kingdom while doing those things?"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Don\u2019t be fooled by those who speak their empty words and deceptive
        teachings telling you otherwise. This is what brings God\u2019s anger upon
        the rebellious! "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Don\u2019t listen to them or live like them at all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Once your life was full of sin\u2019s darkness, but now you have
        the very light of our Lord shining through you because of your union with
        him. Your mission is to live as children flooded with his revelation-light! "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the supernatural fruits of his light [[COMMENT(0)]] will be seen
        in you\u2014goodness, righteousness, and truth. "
      comments:
      - number: 5:9
        content: "  Some Greek manuscripts have \u201CSpirit.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Then you will learn to choose what is beautiful to our Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And don\u2019t even associate with the servants of darkness because
        they have no fruit in them; instead, reveal truth to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The very things they do in secret are too vile and filthy to even
        mention. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Whatever the revelation-light exposes, it will also correct, and
        everything that reveals truth is light to the soul. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 5:13
        content: "  Or \u201Ceverything revealed becomes light.\u201D    "
    - name: "14: Living in God\u2019s Wisdom"
      title: "Living in God\u2019s Wisdom"
      number: 14
      content: "This is why the Scripture says,\u201CArise, you sleeper! Rise up
        from your coffin and the Anointed One will shine his light into you!\u201D
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 5:14
        content: '  See  ;  ;  ;  .    '
    - name: '15-16: '
      title: 
      number: 15-16
      content: 'So be very careful how you live, not being like those with no understanding,
        but live honorably with true wisdom, for we are living in evil times. Take
        full advantage of every day as you spend your life for his purposes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15-16: '
      title: 
      number: 15-16
      content: 'So be very careful how you live, not being like those with no understanding,
        but live honorably with true wisdom, for we are living in evil times. Take
        full advantage of every day as you spend your life for his purposes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And don\u2019t live foolishly for then you will have discernment
        to fully understand God\u2019s will. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And don\u2019t get drunk with wine, which is rebellion; [[COMMENT(0)]]
        instead be filled continually with the Holy Spirit.   "
      comments:
      - number: 5:18
        content: "  The Aramaic can be translated \u201Cthe wine of the prodigal.\u201D
          The Greek is \u201Creckless living\u201D or \u201Cdebauchery.\u201D     
          Or \u201Cbe inebriated in the Spirit\u2019s fullness.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And your hearts will overflow with a joyful song to the Lord. Keep
        speaking to each other with words of Scripture, singing the Psalms with praises
        and spontaneous songs given by the Spirit! [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 5:19
        content: "  Or \u201Cspiritual songs.\u201D There is no other song more spiritual
          than the Song of Songs. Perhaps Paul was encouraging the church to sing
          and rejoice in the greatest of all songs.    "
    - name: '20: Loving Relationships'
      title: Loving Relationships
      number: 20
      content: Always give thanks to Father God for every person [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        he brings into your life in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ.
      comments:
      - number: 5:20
        content: "  The Greek text is ambiguous; it can mean \u201Cgive thanks for
          all things\u201D or \u201Cfor all people.\u201D The Aramaic is quite specific\u2014\u201Cfor
          all people.\u201D    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And out of your reverence for Christ be supportive of each other
        in love. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For wives, this means being devoted [[COMMENT(0)]] to your husbands
        like you are tenderly devoted to our Lord, '
      comments:
      - number: 5:22
        content: "  The Greek word for \u201Csubmit,\u201D or \u201Csupportive,\u201D
          is not found in v.  . It is literally \u201CWives, with your husbands.\u201D    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'for the husband provides leadership for the wife, just as Christ
        provides leadership for his church, as the Savior and Reviver [[COMMENT(0)]]
        of the body. '
      comments:
      - number: 5:23
        content: "  The Aramaic word used here can be translated \u201CSavior\u201D
          or \u201CReviver.\u201D This translation includes both concepts.    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: In the same way the church is devoted to Christ, let the wives be
        devoted to their husbands in everything.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And to the husbands, you are to demonstrate love for your wives with
        the same tender devotion that Christ demonstrated to us, his bride. [[COMMENT(0)]]
        For he died for us, sacrificing himself '
      comments:
      - number: 5:25
        content: "  Or \u201Cchurch.\u201D    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'to make us holy and pure, cleansing us through the showering of the
        pure water of the Word of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "All that he does in us is designed to make us a mature church for
        his pleasure, until we become a source of praise to him\u2014glorious and
        radiant, [[COMMENT(0)]] beautiful and holy, without fault or flaw. "
      comments:
      - number: 5:27
        content: "  The Greek word for \u201Cradiance\u201D () can also mean \u201Cgorgeous,\u201D
          \u201Chonorable,\u201D \u201Cesteemed,\u201D \u201Csplendid,\u201D \u201Cinfused
          with glory.\u201D This is what Christ\u2019s love will do to you. (See 
          , Gr. 1741.)      The Greek text has \u201Cwithout any wrinkle.\u201D The
          Aramaic can be translated \u201Cwithout chips or knots.\u201D    "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Husbands have the obligation of loving and caring for their wives
        the same way they love and care for their own bodies, for to love your wife
        is to love your own self. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "No one abuses his own body, but pampers it\u2014serving and satisfying
        its needs. That\u2019s exactly what Christ does for his church! "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: He serves and satisfies us  [[COMMENT(0)]] as members of his body.
      comments:
      - number: 5:30
        content: '  Inferred from v.    and made explicit here.    '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For this reason a man is to leave his father and his mother and lovingly
        hold to his wife, since the two have become joined as one flesh. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 5:31
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Marriage is the beautiful design of the Almighty, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        a great mystery  of Christ and his church. '
      comments:
      - number: 5:32
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic.      Or \u201Cmegamystery.\u201D
          No book of the Bible unveils more of this great megamystery than does the
          Song of Songs.  "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: So every married man should be gracious to his wife just as he is
        gracious to himself. And every wife should be tenderly devoted to her husband.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Love in Our Families and Workplaces'
      title: Love in Our Families and Workplaces
      number: 1
      content: Children, if you want to be wise, listen to your parents and do what
        they tell you, and the Lord [[COMMENT(0)]] will help you.
      comments:
      - number: 6:1
        content: "  Or \u201Cthrough our Lord.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For the commandment, \u201CHonor your father and your mother,\u201D
        was the first of the Ten Commandments with a promise attached: "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CYou will prosper [[COMMENT(0)]] and live a long, full life
        if you honor your parents.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 6:3
        content: "  Or \u201Cit will go beautifully for you.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Fathers, don\u2019t exasperate your children, [[COMMENT(0)]] but
        raise them up with loving discipline and counsel that brings the revelation
        of our Lord."
      comments:
      - number: 6:4
        content: '  In other words, fathers should show consideration for the different
          levels of understanding and experience that children possess, dealing with
          them at their level, or risk causing them loads of heartache.    '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Those who are employed should listen to their employers [[COMMENT(0)]]
        and obey their instructions with great respect and honor.  Serve them with
        humility in your hearts as though you were working for the Master. '
      comments:
      - number: 6:5
        content: "  Literally \u201Cservants should obey their caretakers.\u201D     
          Or \u201Cwith trembling.\u201D      Or \u201Cthe Messiah.\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Always do what is right and not only when others are watching, so
        that you may please Christ as his servants by doing his will. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Serve [[COMMENT(0)]] your employers wholeheartedly and with love,
        as though you were serving Christ and not men. '
      comments:
      - number: 6:7
        content: "  Or \u201Cminister to them.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Be assured that anything you do that is beautiful and excellent will
        be repaid by our Lord, whether you are an employee or an employer.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Spiritual Warfare'
      title: Spiritual Warfare
      number: 9
      content: And to the caretakers of the flock [[COMMENT(0)]] I say, do what is
        right with your people by forgiving them when they offend you, for you know
        there is a Master in heaven that shows no favoritism.
      comments:
      - number: 6:9
        content: "  As translated literally from the Aramaic. The \u201Ccaretakers
          of the flock\u201D can refer to both leadership in the church and in the
          workplace. The Greek text states \u201Cmasters, do the same things to them,
          and give up threatening.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now my beloved ones, I have saved these most important truths for
        last: Be supernaturally infused with strength through your life-union with
        the Lord Jesus. Stand victorious with the force [[COMMENT(0)]] of his explosive
        power flowing in and through you.'
      comments:
      - number: 6:10
        content: "  Or \u201Cweapons.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Put on God\u2019s complete set of armor [[COMMENT(0)]] provided for
        us, so that you will be protected as you fight against the evil strategies
        of the accuser!   "
      comments:
      - number: 6:11
        content: "  See  .      Or \u201Cthe devil.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Your hand-to-hand combat is not with human beings, but with the highest
        principalities and authorities operating in rebellion under the heavenly
        realms. [[COMMENT(0)]] For they are a powerful class of demon-gods  and evil
        spirits that hold  this dark world in bondage. '
      comments:
      - number: 6:12
        content: "  Or literally \u201Cunder heaven.\u201D      The classical Greek
          word used here is often used to refer to conjuring up pagan deities\u2014supreme
          powers of darkness mentioned in occult rituals.      Or \u201Cpossessors
          of this dark world.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Because of this, you must wear all the armor that God provides so
        you\u2019re protected as you confront the slanderer, [[COMMENT(0)]] for you
        are destined for all things  and will rise victorious."
      comments:
      - number: 6:13
        content: "  Or \u201Cdevil.\u201D      As translated from the Aramaic. The
          Greek text can be translated \u201Cafter you have conquered, you can stand
          in victory.\u201D    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Put on truth as a belt to strengthen you to stand in triumph. Put
        on holiness as the protective armor that covers your heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Stand on your feet alert, then you\u2019ll always be ready to share
        the blessings of peace."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'In every battle, take faith as your wrap-around shield, for it is
        able to extinguish the blazing arrows coming at you from the evil one! [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 6:16
        content: '  The poetic language Paul uses here is likely a reference to 
          .    '
    - name: '17-18: '
      title: 
      number: 17-18
      content: "Embrace the power of salvation\u2019s full deliverance, like a helmet
        to protect your thoughts from lies. And take the mighty razor-sharp Spirit-sword
        [[COMMENT(0)]] of the spoken word of God.Pray passionately  in the Spirit,
        as you constantly intercede with every form of prayer at all times. Pray
        the blessings of God upon all his believers. "
      comments:
      - number: "6:17\u201318"
        content: "  This is the Greek word  , which was a razor-sharp Roman sword
          used in close combat.      Or \u201Call desires.\u201D    "
    - name: '17-18: '
      title: 
      number: 17-18
      content: "Embrace the power of salvation\u2019s full deliverance, like a helmet
        to protect your thoughts from lies. And take the mighty razor-sharp Spirit-sword
        [[COMMENT(0)]] of the spoken word of God.Pray passionately  in the Spirit,
